<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2974] writeToParcel throws NPE for optional enum fields</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2974</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The recent change to the Java compiler added generated Android compatible, parcelable Thrift objects.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/commit/f9b8f5e64137248ea2a1b95312916491d23ab94a#diff-80220be8df49fb98fe5f899544d8368dR1569&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/commit/f9b8f5e64137248ea2a1b95312916491d23ab94a#diff-80220be8df49fb98fe5f899544d8368dR1569&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, for optional enum fields that are null, getValue() will throw an NPE because no checks are made that the enum is set before being written.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12771823">THRIFT-2974</key>
